'''Buduka Dylan Batubinsika''' (born 15 February 1996) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Super League Greece]] club [[Athlitiki Enosi Larissa F.C.|AEL]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

==Club career==
Batubinska played as a youngster for [[Paris Saint-Germain Academy]]. In 2014 he began playing for the club's [[reserve team]], capping 52 times and scoring twice.{{Citation needed|date=June 2024}}

On 13 July 2017, Batubinsika joined [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Antwerp]] from the [[Jupiler Pro League|Belgian First Division A]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sporza.be/permalink/1.3023850 |title=Antwerp plukt vier spelers weg bij onder meer PSG en Saint-Etienne |trans-title=Antwerp snatches four players away from amongst others PSG and Saint-Etienne |language=Dutch |date=2017-07-13 |publisher=sporza.be }}{{Dead link|date=December 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> During his 4-year spell with the club he capped 73 times and scored 3 goals, and won the [[2019–20 Belgian Cup|2019–20]] [[Belgian Cup]].

On 23 July 2021, he signed a four-year contract with Portuguese top-tier [[Primeira Liga]] club [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]]|url=https://www.fcfamalicao.pt/dylan-batubinsika-assina-por-quatro-temporadas/|title=DYLAN BATUBINSIKA ASSINA POR QUATRO TEMPORADAS|date=23 July 2021|accessdate=21 September 2021|language=pt}}</ref>

On 31 August 2022, Batubinsika was loaned to Israeli top-tier [[Israeli Premier League|Ligat Ha'Al]] club [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]] for the rest of the 2022–23 season, with an option to make the signing permanent.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Walla!|Walla! Sports]]|url=https://sports.walla.co.il/item/3527316|title=מכבי חיפה החתימה את הבלם דילן בטובינסיקה|date=31 August 2022|accessdate=12 October 2022|language=he}}</ref> On 3 September 2022 he made his debut for the club in a 2–1 victory over [[Hapoel Be'er Sheva F.C.|Hapoel Be'er Sheva]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2024}}

On 21 July 2023, [[Ligue 2]] side [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]] announced the signing of Batubinsika on a two-year deal, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=21 July 2023 |title=Communiqué officiel : Dylan Batubinsika est Stéphanois! |trans-title=Official announcement: Dylan Batubinsika is Stéphanois! |url=https://www.asse.fr/fr/actualites/dylan-batubinsika-est-stephanois--ac34732 |access-date=2023-07-26 |website=ASSE.fr |language=fr}}</ref>

On 26 January 2026, Batubinsika joined [[Super League Greece]] club [[Athlitiki Enosi Larissa F.C.|AEL]] on a six-month contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 January 2026 |title=Παίκτης της ΠΑΕ ΑΕΛ Novibet o Ντιλάν Μπατουμπινσικά |trans-title=Dylan Batubinsika is an AEL player |url=https://www.aelfc.gr/2026/01/paiktis-tis-pae-ael-novibet-o-ntilan-batoumpinsika/ |access-date=27 January 2026 |publisher=[[Athlitiki Enosi Larissa F.C.|AEL]] |language=el}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Batubinsika is of DR Congolese descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://voila.cd/foot-infos-1ere-journee-pro-league-belgique-bolingi-marque/|title=FOOT-INFOS : 1ere JOURNEE PRO LEAGUE BELGIQUE, BOLINGI MARQUE…. – VOILA NIGHT|date=2 August 2017|publisher=|access-date=24 August 2018|archive-date=15 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215204805/https://voila.cd/foot-infos-1ere-journee-pro-league-belgique-bolingi-marque/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was called up to the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] for 5. Matchday in Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers in June 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/amical-la-rd-congo-se-rassure-avant-le-gabon|title=Amical : la RD Congo se rassure avant le Gabon|date=June 14, 2023|website=afrik-foot.com}}</ref>

On 27 December 2023, he was selected from the list of 24 Congolese players selected by [[Sébastien Desabre]] to compete in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].

